00:22:35,688 --> 00:22:39,223
Should I be, uh...
i don't know...

365
00:22:39,225 --> 00:22:42,026
uh, treating you any different?

366
00:22:42,028 --> 00:22:44,495
Please don't.

367
00:22:44,497 --> 00:22:46,197
Well, you let me know.

368
00:22:46,199 --> 00:22:47,698
Mm-hmm.

369
00:22:52,205 --> 00:22:55,539
Better get inside
and take my sugar pills.

370
00:22:55,541 --> 00:22:56,907
[ Chuckles ]

371
00:22:56,909 --> 00:22:59,243
Dispatch:
State car 18, come back. Over.

372
00:22:59,245 --> 00:23:01,145
Uh... That's me.

373
00:23:01,147 --> 00:23:03,214
Yeah, I know.

374
00:23:03,216 --> 00:23:04,648
Go.

375
00:23:04,650 --> 00:23:06,550
I'll be fine.

376
00:23:14,927 --> 00:23:16,861
[ Door opens, closes ]

377
00:23:16,863 --> 00:23:19,764
Indian buck...
had like a rat face.

378
00:23:19,766 --> 00:23:21,766
Didn't much like
the look of him.

379
00:23:21,768 --> 00:23:24,335
Scared me...
a little.

380
00:23:24,337 --> 00:23:25,870
Sorry.

381
00:23:25,872 --> 00:23:28,205
Took Betsy to a specialist.

382
00:23:28,207 --> 00:23:29,907
And?

383
00:23:29,909 --> 00:23:33,344
Uh, well, uh, there's a trial...

384
00:23:33,346 --> 00:23:35,679
um, clinical.

385
00:23:35,681 --> 00:23:40,451
New drug, so, uh,
we signed up for that.

386
00:23:40,453 --> 00:23:42,520
Okay.
What'd I miss here?

387
00:23:42,522 --> 00:23:44,922
Uh, well, uh...

388
00:23:44,924 --> 00:23:48,058
This... this Indian fella
put a scare to Sonny.

389
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:51,529
Luckily, Karl was nearby,
stressin' the plumbing.

390
00:23:51,531 --> 00:23:53,898
[ Chuckling ]
Scared the Indian off.

391
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:56,066
What was he doing exactly,
this, uh, Indian?

392
00:23:56,068 --> 00:23:57,601
Well, I found him
out here in the bay,

393
00:23:57,603 --> 00:23:59,069
looking over Ed's car...
seemed real interested.

394
00:23:59,071 --> 00:24:01,071
Ed renner?

395
00:24:01,073 --> 00:24:02,306
No, ed blumquist...

396
00:24:02,308 --> 00:24:03,641
you know,
works bud's butcher shop.

397
00:24:03,643 --> 00:24:05,543
Yeah. Wife's car, technically.

398
00:24:05,545 --> 00:24:08,012
Got some front-end damage
you can see.

399
00:24:11,584 --> 00:24:14,919
As in...
Front-end damage

400
00:24:14,921 --> 00:24:16,821
like the kind you get
running down a gunman

401
00:24:16,823 --> 00:24:18,889
who just shot up three people
at the waffle hut?

402
00:24:18,891 --> 00:24:20,758
The what now?

403
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:24,562
Uh, no, no, this was,
uh, from an accident yesterday.

404
00:24:24,564 --> 00:24:26,263
Bluth took the report.

405
00:24:26,265 --> 00:24:31,001
Said the blumquists hit a tree
off ice patch junction,

406
00:24:31,003 --> 00:24:33,337
tree branch went through
the window...

407
00:24:33,339 --> 00:24:35,473
lucky the wife wasn't killed.

408
00:24:38,077 --> 00:24:40,311
Hit it coming and going?

409
00:24:40,313 --> 00:24:42,480
Yeah, yeah, I saw that.

410
00:24:42,482 --> 00:24:44,748
Sonny: Peggy said
garage door bit her in the back.

411
00:24:44,750 --> 00:24:48,686
But I, uh, found bits of wood in the
bumper, so... [ Telephone ringing ]

412
00:24:48,688 --> 00:24:53,023
Not saying she's lying,
but, you know, uh...

413
00:24:53,025 --> 00:24:55,526
Ed: Hey. Burning it
at both ends, huh?

414
00:24:55,528 --> 00:24:57,495
Uh, yeah.

415
00:24:57,497 --> 00:24:59,997
[ Ringing continues ]

416
00:25:02,168 --> 00:25:04,368
You gonna get that?

417
00:25:05,538 --> 00:25:07,771
Yeah.

418
00:25:18,784 --> 00:25:22,052
[ Choir singing in Latin ]

419
00:25:38,838 --> 00:25:42,406
[ Singing continues ]

420
00:26:10,269 --> 00:26:12,670
Thank you for sitting with me
here today

421
00:26:12,672 --> 00:26:16,173
and for giving us time
to consider your offer.

422
00:26:16,175 --> 00:26:18,909
I've asked the bank
to arbitrate as neutral party.

423
00:26:20,279 --> 00:26:21,779
Whatever makes you comfortable.

424
00:26:21,781 --> 00:26:23,013
This is your town.

425
00:26:24,283 --> 00:26:25,916
Where's Mr. milligan?

426
00:26:25,918 --> 00:26:29,086
Another matter,
back in Kansas City.

427
00:26:29,088 --> 00:26:32,790
So, we've given you 48 hours
to consider.

428
00:26:32,792 --> 00:26:35,025
Do we have a deal?

429
00:26:35,027 --> 00:26:36,527
No.

430
00:26:36,529 --> 00:26:40,965
But I have a counteroffer,
a respectful one.

431
00:26:40,967 --> 00:26:44,468
Instead of a straight sale,
us to you,

432
00:26:44,470 --> 00:26:47,938
we pay you $1 million cash money

433
00:26:47,940 --> 00:26:52,076
plus 20% of our territory
in Minnesota.

434
00:26:52,078 --> 00:26:53,911
We also discount
transportation fees

435
00:26:53,913 --> 00:26:58,449
on all Kansas City merchandise,
25% for the first 5 years.

436
00:26:58,451 --> 00:27:00,918
In exchange,

437
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:04,989
we retain full control
of our remaining operations...

438
00:27:04,991 --> 00:27:09,126
the gerhardt family
still runs north Dakota

439
00:27:09,128 --> 00:27:12,796
but with Kansas City.

440
00:27:12,798 --> 00:27:19,470
Partnership, not a sale...
that's our offer to you.

441
00:27:19,472 --> 00:27:21,405
And we believe
it's more than fair.

442
00:27:23,809 --> 00:27:25,509
I see.

443
00:27:25,511 --> 00:27:26,977
Now...

444
00:27:29,315 --> 00:27:31,815
I don't know.

445
00:27:31,817 --> 00:27:34,818
Maybe, when you look at me,
you see an old woman,

446
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:37,688
and I am 61.

447
00:27:37,690 --> 00:27:42,426
I've borne six children,
had three miscarriages.

448
00:27:42,428 --> 00:27:44,328
Two of my sons are here today.

449
00:27:44,330 --> 00:27:47,498
Two were stillborn.

450
00:27:47,500 --> 00:27:52,770
My firstborn, elron,
killed in Korea...

451
00:27:52,772 --> 00:27:57,608
gook sniper
took off half his head.

452
00:27:57,610 --> 00:28:00,644
The point is...

453
00:28:00,646 --> 00:28:05,182
Don't assume, just because
I'm an old woman,

454
00:28:05,184 --> 00:28:09,286
that my back is weak
and my stomach's not strong.

455
00:28:09,288 --> 00:28:12,990
I make this counter because a
deal is always better than war.

456
00:28:12,992 --> 00:28:15,693
But no mistake...

457
00:28:15,695 --> 00:28:19,563
we'll fight to keep what's ours
to the last man.

458
00:28:19,565 --> 00:28:23,400
[ Breathes deeply ]

459
00:28:23,402 --> 00:28:26,637
You're a good woman.

460
00:28:26,639 --> 00:28:28,739
I wish I'd known your husband.

461
00:28:28,741 --> 00:28:30,374
No.

462
00:28:30,376 --> 00:28:32,376
My husband would've killed you
where you stood

463
00:28:32,378 --> 00:28:34,678
the first time you met.

464
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:38,015
So be glad
you're talking to his wife.

465
00:28:38,017 --> 00:28:40,551
And that's what I'm glad for.

466
00:28:43,656 --> 00:28:49,760
And if it were up to me,
I would take your counter...

467
00:28:49,762 --> 00:28:51,929
Partner up...

468
00:28:51,931 --> 00:28:56,066
Except I got to admit,
I-i just wonder,

469
00:28:56,068 --> 00:29:00,237
if we make this deal,
split the territory,

470
00:29:00,239 --> 00:29:02,406
we move in,

471
00:29:02,408 --> 00:29:05,609
can you guarantee
your boys will abide?

472
00:29:05,611 --> 00:29:08,746
My sons listen to their mother.

473
00:29:08,748 --> 00:29:11,115
Good.

474
00:29:11,117 --> 00:29:13,050
Okay.

475
00:29:13,052 --> 00:29:17,521
Except here are two of my men

476
00:29:17,523 --> 00:29:21,458
assaulted just this morning in
the appropriation of doughnuts

477
00:29:21,460 --> 00:29:23,927
by your oldest...

478
00:29:23,929 --> 00:29:27,131
attacked in peacetime,

479
00:29:27,133 --> 00:29:29,700
during a period of deliberation,

480
00:29:29,702 --> 00:29:32,202
without provocation.

481
00:29:32,204 --> 00:29:33,937
Oh, I was provoked.

482
00:29:33,939 --> 00:29:35,038
Hush.

483
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:37,541
My sons will abide.

484
00:29:37,543 --> 00:29:39,943
Ah, s-s-see,
that... that...

485
00:29:39,945 --> 00:29:42,412
that's the problem
with a family business.

486
00:29:42,414 --> 00:29:48,218
Now, if one of my men defies me,
puts a deal in jeopardy,

487
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:50,420
I take his arm.

488
00:29:50,422 --> 00:29:53,590
If he talks out of turn,
I take his tongue.

489
00:29:53,592 --> 00:29:57,795
But you... your children,
your grandchildren...

490
00:29:57,797 --> 00:30:02,432
what are you willing to do
to show us you're committed?

491
00:30:02,434 --> 00:30:05,002
I'll deal with my son.

492
00:30:05,004 --> 00:30:06,503
This partnership will hold.

493
00:30:06,505 --> 00:30:08,405
Oh, come on, you're gonna
let this guy come here

494
00:30:08,407 --> 00:30:10,941
and disrespect us, disrespect pop?
Floyd: Quiet!

495
00:30:10,943 --> 00:30:13,844
Bunch of fruits in ties and pocket
protectors. Take him out now!

496
00:30:13,846 --> 00:30:15,679
I'll pick my teeth with you.
Take him out!

497
00:30:15,681 --> 00:30:17,581
I'll pick my freakin' teeth
with you!

498
00:30:17,583 --> 00:30:19,049
Get off me!
[ Door closes ]

499
00:30:23,856 --> 00:30:25,923
I apologize.

500
00:30:25,925 --> 00:30:28,325
He's a proud man.

501
00:30:28,327 --> 00:30:32,529
His father built an empire,
and he just wants what's his.

502
00:30:32,531 --> 00:30:34,698
He'll fall into line.

503
00:30:34,700 --> 00:30:36,466
No.

504
00:30:36,468 --> 00:30:38,869
I don't think he will.

505
00:30:49,982 --> 00:30:52,049
Hold up.

506
00:31:00,492 --> 00:31:03,293
Who's the dumb-ass?

507
00:31:05,731 --> 00:31:09,366
Go around to the passenger seat.

508
00:31:09,368 --> 00:31:11,401
Slide across.

509
00:31:15,374 --> 00:31:16,740
Hurry up.

510
00:31:16,742 --> 00:31:19,076
Yeah, yeah.

511
00:31:25,918 --> 00:31:29,052
[ Engine sputtering ]

512
00:31:29,054 --> 00:31:32,089
[ Ominous music plays ]

513
00:31:34,393 --> 00:31:38,061
[ Sputtering continues ]

514
00:31:57,783 --> 00:32:01,351
[ Vehicle departs ]

515
00:32:01,353 --> 00:32:02,619
Ollie:
Well, what's the holdup?

516
00:32:02,621 --> 00:32:04,688
